Oh, hi.

13:42.555 --> 13:44.649
You have one, too,
and they know each other?

13:44.758 --> 13:46.692
Fonz, this is,
this is Lori Beth, here.

13:46.793 --> 13:49.091
I'm sorry we didn't
meet before 10:00.

13:49.195 --> 13:50.754
Hey, that's all right.

13:50.864 --> 13:53.094
The Fonz don't
turn into no pumpkin.

13:53.199 --> 13:55.190
Hey, I gotta tell
you something, Rich.

13:55.301 --> 13:57.895
I want to introduce you
to Christy Riggenheimer.

13:58.004 --> 13:59.631
This is a very cool chick.

13:59.739 --> 14:01.639
The things that she did to me

14:01.741 --> 14:03.334
made me feel good all over!

14:03.443 --> 14:04.342
Oh, Fonz, Fonz...

14:04.444 --> 14:05.343
Fonz, I don't think Lori Beth

14:05.445 --> 14:06.571
really wants to hear about that.

14:06.679 --> 14:07.908
Oh, yeah, before
I knew what was happening...

14:08.014 --> 14:09.482
- Fonz! -...before I knew
what was happening,

14:09.582 --> 14:12.779
I was applying for
my own "liberry" card

14:12.886 --> 14:15.480
and checking out
my very first book.

14:15.588 --> 14:17.522
Oh... I thought
you were gonna say, uh...

14:17.624 --> 14:18.955
something else. I...

14:19.058 --> 14:20.389
Oh, I'll tell you
something, Rich.

14:20.493 --> 14:23.827
You should've heard
what she said to me.

14:25.064 --> 14:26.589
She is the first chick--

14:26.699 --> 14:28.963
I'm talking the first chick--

14:29.068 --> 14:30.729
that ever said

14:30.837 --> 14:34.398
that I stimulated her
intellectually.

14:36.409 --> 14:39.606
And now I got
my own "liberry" card.

14:39.712 --> 14:41.771
- Whoa.
- Wait...

14:41.881 --> 14:43.781
y-you went to the library
all those years,

14:43.883 --> 14:45.112
and-and you never got a card?

14:45.218 --> 14:46.208
No, I never thought

14:46.319 --> 14:47.878
they'd give it to a guy like me.

14:47.987 --> 14:49.819
But do you know
there's a card for everybody?

14:49.923 --> 14:51.084
That's right.

14:51.191 --> 14:53.683
Everybody is allowed to read.

14:53.793 --> 14:55.784
Who would've thought
such a thing?

14:57.096 --> 14:58.359
Richie, I hate to alarm you,

14:58.465 --> 14:59.830
but I think
I'm gonna be hysterical.

14:59.933 --> 15:01.162
All right, all right,
don't worry.

15:01.267 --> 15:03.201
If anybody can get us
out of this, it's Fonzie.

15:03.303 --> 15:04.930
Correctamundo.

15:05.038 --> 15:07.268
All right, school's out,
time for action.

15:07.373 --> 15:08.499
The window.

15:08.608 --> 15:09.803
Oh, you're not gonna
be able to open that.

15:09.909 --> 15:10.842
It's painted shut.

15:10.944 --> 15:13.311
Ye of little faith.

15:18.318 --> 15:20.343
Wait...

15:20.453 --> 15:22.251
that's a long way down there.

15:22.355 --> 15:23.254
What do you think?

15:23.356 --> 15:24.721
Well, I think we could make it,

15:24.824 --> 15:27.384
if you want to spend the next
six years in plaster pants.

15:27.494 --> 15:29.258
- Oh, no, no...
- No.

15:29.362 --> 15:30.557
RICHIE:
Hey, hey, Fonz.

15:30.663 --> 15:32.062
- Yeah?
- Fonz, I got an idea.

15:32.165 --> 15:33.758
We could take the mattresses,
right, throw 'em out the window

15:33.867 --> 15:35.130
and use those to break our fall.

15:35.235 --> 15:37.135
Or-or, better yet,
we could take the sheets, see?

15:37.237 --> 15:38.398
We could, we could rip 'em up.

15:38.505 --> 15:39.563
We could tie 'em together,

15:39.672 --> 15:40.798
-make a rope and climb down.
- Yeah. -Yeah!

15:40.907 --> 15:42.204
Boy, I'm really starting
to think now, Fonz.

15:42.308 --> 15:43.332
- Uh, Rich?
- Hmm?

15:43.443 --> 15:46.105
Have you no respect
for state property?

15:46.212 --> 15:48.078
Well, Fonzie,
you have to do something.

15:48.181 --> 15:50.172
Right! Let's party.

15:51.184 --> 15:52.618
Party?!
Fonz, if you get caught,

15:52.719 --> 15:54.016
you're just gonna get yelled at.

15:54.120 --> 15:55.110
The three of us
could be expelled.

15:55.221 --> 15:56.450
- My father'll kill me.
- Expelled.

15:56.556 --> 15:57.955
- You know what that would
be, Fonz? -Hey, hey, hey.

15:58.057 --> 15:58.990
Hold it, hold it, hold it.

15:59.092 --> 16:00.992
Freshmen, ugh...

16:01.094 --> 16:02.562
They're not gonna expel you.

16:02.662 --> 16:04.596
They might suspend you
for about a year.

16:04.697 --> 16:06.495
Oh... oh, what a relief.

16:06.599 --> 16:08.033
Fonz, we gotta do something.

16:08.134 --> 16:09.397
All right, think a bit.

16:09.502 --> 16:11.129
All right.

16:11.237 --> 16:13.069
- All right, here's a plan.
- What?

16:13.172 --> 16:15.368
Uh... if we can get
down to the first floor,

16:15.475 --> 16:16.704
we could probably crawl out

16:16.809 --> 16:18.277
a-a supply room window
or something.

16:18.378 --> 16:19.573
- Couldn't we?
- Yeah, great!

16:19.679 --> 16:21.147
Christy and I'll run down
and check it out!

16:21.247 --> 16:22.339
<i>Okay, hum!-</i>

16:22.448 --> 16:24.439
We don't have too much time
till bed check.

16:26.886 --> 16:28.877
You're an absolute genius.

16:31.724 --> 16:34.022
(Wry chuckle)

16:38.398 --> 16:41.527
Takes me a while, but, uh...
I come through. (chuckles)

16:42.569 --> 16:44.298
Einstein, huh?

16:44.404 --> 16:46.736
Well, listen, tell me, Albert,

16:46.839 --> 16:48.807
how do you figure
we're gonna get out that door,

16:48.908 --> 16:50.239
down the stairs
and through the window

16:50.343 --> 16:52.812
without getting nailed?

16:52.912 --> 16:54.437
All right, all right,
just a second.

16:54.547 --> 16:56.037
Albert's really cooking now.

16:58.384 --> 16:59.476
(imitates dog barking)

17:09.628 --> 17:11.256
Hey, Uh. try again.

17:11.364 --> 17:13.263
Oh, Fonz, Fonz, these are nice.

17:13.366 --> 17:14.265
Quality merchandise.

17:14.367 --> 17:15.528
Here, you take first pick.

17:15.635 --> 17:17.296
I want to tell you something--

17:17.403 --> 17:19.598
the judge's decision is final,

17:19.705 --> 17:21.195
'cause the Fonz

17:21.307 --> 17:23.298
don't wear dresses.

17:27.747 --> 17:30.011
Fonz, look, lo-lot-lots
of men wear dresses.

17:30.116 --> 17:32.016
Well, they do.

17:32.118 --> 17:33.711
Uh... Tony Curtis.

17:33.820 --> 17:35.288
And Jack Lemmon.

17:35.388 --> 17:37.117
Uncle Milty!

17:40.927 --> 17:43.589
Davy Crockett
never wore a dress.

17:44.764 --> 17:45.663
What's he got to do with it?

17:45.765 --> 17:46.960
Everything-

17:47.066 --> 17:49.398
When Davy Crockett
was trapped inside the Alamo,

17:49.502 --> 17:51.937
he could've worn
a dress to escape,

17:52.038 --> 17:53.267
but he didn't, oh, no.

17:53.373 --> 17:55.398
Not the King of
the Wild Frontier.

17:55.508 --> 17:57.476
He stuck it out

17:57.577 --> 18:00.308
and so will the Fonz.

18:01.614 --> 18:03.844
But Davy Crockett
died at the Alamo.

18:05.685 --> 18:06.584
Good point.

18:06.686 --> 18:07.881
Give that nightie.

18:26.973 --> 18:28.873
Just level with me, Rich.

18:28.975 --> 18:31.103
- Am I little lopsided?
-(laughs)

18:32.612 --> 18:33.943
No.

18:34.047 --> 18:35.879
(laughing):
I... I can't wait...

18:35.982 --> 18:37.950
I can't wait
to tell Ralph and Potsie

18:38.051 --> 18:39.075
-that the Fonz...
- Hey!

18:40.386 --> 18:41.410
I want to tell you something.

18:41.521 --> 18:42.682
If you tell those two turnips,

18:42.789 --> 18:44.188
if you tell anybody...

18:45.391 --> 18:47.655
How can I be tough
wearing a nightie?

18:49.929 --> 18:50.919
Yeah...

18:51.030 --> 18:52.156
You don't have to worry, Fonz.

18:52.265 --> 18:53.699
Your secret's safe with me.

18:53.800 --> 18:55.393
(insistent knocking on door)

18:55.501 --> 18:57.060
WOMAN:
Mrs. Dunbar! Bed check time!

18:57.170 --> 18:58.069
(whispering):
Bed check, Fonz!

18:58.171 --> 18:59.730
Will you calm down?

19:01.007 --> 19:01.906
All right, look.

19:02.008 --> 19:03.373
If we get past her,

19:03.476 --> 19:05.137
we are home safe, all right?

19:05.244 --> 19:08.077
- Right.
- Cool it.

19:08.181 --> 19:10.445
(high-pitched):
Just one second, Mrs. Dunbar.

19:11.818 --> 19:14.150
We're-we're not decent.

19:14.253 --> 19:15.687
Oh! Oh...

19:17.857 --> 19:19.825
- Very good idea, Fonz.
- Yeah, now what do we do?

19:19.926 --> 19:21.394
Uh, hey. Get under the covers.

19:21.494 --> 19:22.689
Yeah. That's my bed.

19:22.795 --> 19:24.229
All right, it's yours.

19:24.330 --> 19:26.321
I want to tell you something,
this is very exciting.

19:28.034 --> 19:28.933
The lights, the lights!

19:29.035 --> 19:31.504
Get the ligh... what is this?

19:31.604 --> 19:32.662
(pounding on door)

19:32.772 --> 19:34.399
MRS. DUNBAR:
What's going on in there?

19:34.507 --> 19:36.703
(high-pitched): You can come
in now, Mrs. Dunbar.

19:40.246 --> 19:41.441
Took so long I was
beginning to think

19:41.547 --> 19:42.605
you might have a man in here.

19:42.715 --> 19:44.376
(both squeal, shudder)

19:46.052 --> 19:47.850
That ain't funny.

19:47.954 --> 19:50.389
All righty, now, I understand
one of you girls is sick.

19:53.059 --> 19:55.050
FONZIE:
Aaayh... (high-pitched squeal)

19:56.295 --> 19:57.660
What's the big idea, Leona?

19:57.764 --> 19:59.459
Trying to infect the whole dorm?

19:59.565 --> 20:01.363
- Let's have a look-see.
- FONZIE: No, no!

20:01.467 --> 20:03.458
GIRL: Come on, girls,
there's a panty raid!

20:03.569 --> 20:05.298
-(girls screaming)
- Panty raid!

20:05.404 --> 20:06.872
Don't panic, girls.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.605
Sergeant Dunbar,
reporting for duty!

20:17.116 --> 20:19.107
All right, just calm down.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.023
Jllmp?
Jllmp!

20:25.424 --> 20:27.415
Panty raid!

20:32.765 --> 20:34.358
FONZIE:
Yeah.

20:37.203 --> 20:41.003
You just don't
let 'em know it is us.

20:41.107 --> 20:43.439
Hi, girls.

20:43.543 --> 20:45.568
Been waiting for us, huh, girls?

20:46.779 --> 20:48.304
Give us your underwear!

20:48.414 --> 20:49.677
This is a panty raid!

20:49.782 --> 20:51.272
FONZIE (high-pitched):
Oh, don't hurt us, you guys!

20:51.384 --> 20:53.375
(shrieking)

20:55.321 --> 20:56.618
Don't worry.

21:02.895 --> 21:04.294
Don't worry, sweetheart.

21:04.397 --> 21:05.523
We won't hurt you.

21:05.631 --> 21:07.759
Okay, girls, where do you
keep your valuables?

21:07.867 --> 21:08.766
FONZIE:
Oh!

21:13.406 --> 21:16.273
Potsie, look at those girls.

21:17.376 --> 21:18.810
Is this a dorm or a kennel?

21:23.482 --> 21:25.075
You know, Ralph,

21:25.184 --> 21:27.209
the one with
the freckles is cute.

21:27.320 --> 21:29.652
But... but the other one
looks like Fonzie.

21:33.059 --> 21:35.619
Potsie, look!

21:35.728 --> 21:37.719
Boy, she could be
Fonzie's sister.

21:39.031 --> 21:39.964
Look...

21:40.066 --> 21:42.034
don't you mention
this to anybody,

21:42.134 --> 21:43.033
or you'll never eat

21:43.135 --> 21:44.296
solid food again, dig?

21:44.403 --> 21:45.427
- Right.
- Uh-huh.

21:45.538 --> 21:46.437
I'm just glad you guys

21:46.539 --> 21:47.438
showed up, that's all.

21:47.540 --> 21:48.701
Hey, it's Rich, too!

21:48.808 --> 21:50.173
(Ralph laughs)

21:50.276 --> 21:52.836
- Boy, did we pick
the wrong room. -Yeah.

21:52.945 --> 21:55.539
All we're gonna come back with
is two pairs of jockey shorts.

21:56.782 --> 21:57.681
All right, let's go.

21:57.783 --> 21:59.080
- Out the window.
- Aw, come on, Fonz.

21:59.185 --> 22:01.017
- Let us stay, please, come on.
- Wait, aw, come on, Fonz.

22:01.120 --> 22:03.111
This is my first panty raid!

22:03.222 --> 22:05.486
I been waiting for this moment
my whole life, Fonz.

22:05.591 --> 22:06.649
<i>Anything“ do.</i>

22:06.759 --> 22:08.659
A half slip,
a training bra, even.

22:08.761 --> 22:10.786
All right,
you're breaking my heart.

22:10.897 --> 22:11.796
Make it fast.

22:11.898 --> 22:13.889
- Thanks, man.
- Aw, thanks, Fonz!

22:14.901 --> 22:16.926
Aha!

22:17.036 --> 22:20.495
I caught you red-handed,
you panty raiders!

22:20.606 --> 22:22.631
- Duck, Malph!
- Oh, oh, ow!

22:22.742 --> 22:24.267
- Ow!
- You animal!

22:24.377 --> 22:27.347
All right,
out the window, Malph! Go!

22:27.446 --> 22:29.676
- Out! Out! And don't try to...
- Yes, yes, we're going! I'm g...

22:29.782 --> 22:31.580
- Ow! Ow! Ow!
- DUNBAR: Okay, Red.

22:31.684 --> 22:33.277
You... charge!

22:33.386 --> 22:34.911
Run!

22:35.021 --> 22:36.989
(grunting, thumping)

22:37.089 --> 22:39.080
- Tomorrow night.
- Yeah!

22:39.191 --> 22:40.124
Out! Out!

22:40.226 --> 22:42.024
LORI BETH:
See you then!

22:42.128 --> 22:43.926
MRS. DUNBAR:
All right.

22:44.030 --> 22:45.088
Out...

22:45.197 --> 22:47.996
you leather-jacketed hoodlum.

22:53.239 --> 22:56.766
Now, is that any way
to talk, gorgeous?

23:03.282 --> 23:07.719
Don't give me any
of your sweet talk, Slick.

23:26.672 --> 23:29.471
I bid you all a fond adieu.

23:38.584 --> 23:41.019
- Mother Dunbar?
- Mother Dunbar?

23:41.120 --> 23:43.612
Come back, Slick.

23:52.498 --> 23:53.465
Hey, Cunningham.

23:53.566 --> 23:54.624
Oh, hi, Fonz.

23:54.734 --> 23:56.793
So... how was, uh, Homecoming?

23:56.902 --> 23:58.336
Oh, great.

23:58.437 --> 24:00.531
Lori Beth thinks
I'm very mature for a freshman.

24:00.639 --> 24:02.869
That's 'cause she never
saw you in a nightie.

24:02.975 --> 24:04.966
Oh, right.

24:05.077 --> 24:07.409
I'm starting to get the hang
of this-this college stuff.

24:07.513 --> 24:08.412
I knew you would.

24:08.514 --> 24:10.710
Well, here's the camera, Rich.

24:10.816 --> 24:11.749
They're ready now.

24:11.851 --> 24:12.875
More movies?

24:12.985 --> 24:15.317
I'm getting out
of here real quick.

24:15.421 --> 24:17.116
Hey, you know what
I think I'm gonna do?

24:18.457 --> 24:21.256
I think I'm gonna
put my "liberry" card to use.

24:21.360 --> 24:23.351
Whoa...

24:24.897 --> 24:26.331
HOWARD: We're all set
whenever you are, Rich.

24:26.432 --> 24:28.332
All right, uh...
lights, Joan, lights.

24:28.434 --> 24:29.833
Okay.

24:29.935 --> 24:31.198
Ready...

24:31.303 --> 24:32.793
and... action!

24:40.613 --> 24:42.047
Okay, good.

24:43.983 --> 24:46.384
Oh, I got it, I got it.
Pick it up.

24:46.485 --> 24:49.250
-(camera whirring)
-(no voices)

